# Workspace packages

The repo is a **pnpm workspace** (`pnpm-workspace.yaml` → `packages/*`). The Vite app and `api/` stay at the **repo root** for Vercel. After pulling, run **pnpm install** to link workspace packages.

## Package map

| Package | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `@minute-menus/types` | Domain interfaces and enums (`AppMode`, `Dish`, subscriptions, etc.) |
| `@minute-menus/types/db` | Generated Supabase `Database` types (source: `packages/types/src/database.types.ts`) |
| `@minute-menus/logger` | `createLogger(scope)` for API routes and services |
| `@minute-menus/errors` | `getErrorMessage`, `toError`, `throwStepError` (Supabase errors are plain objects) |
| `@minute-menus/currency` | Price formatting, `SUPPORTED_CURRENCIES`, locale detection |
| `@minute-menus/ui` | Loaders, spinners, `SaveChangesButton`, `ButtonSpinner` |
| `@minute-menus/reels` | `ReelCard`, `ReelStrip` (customer reel UI) |
| `@minute-menus/metrics` | Pure analytics builders (`buildAggregatedMetrics`, `buildAnalyticsReport`, time windows) |
| `@minute-menus/menu-persistence` | Menu upsert/sync/delete (`persistMenu`) |
| `@minute-menus/meal-plan-persistence` | Meal plan row upsert and dish link sync |
| `@minute-menus/supabase-service` | Full data layer — `createSupabaseService(client)` |
| `@minute-menus/ai` | Anthropic Claude (analytics reports, marketing copy) |
| `@minute-menus/mailer` | Brevo SMTP `sendMail` (server-side) |
| `@minute-menus/email-templates` | HTML for sold-out, cancel-order, daily-digest emails |
| `@minute-menus/api-helpers` | Vercel handler guards, CORS, payload parsing, internal secret check |
| `@minute-menus/payments` | Razorpay order creation and subscription amount helpers |

## App-root shims (backward compat)

These re-export packages — prefer importing the package directly in new code:

- `services/supabaseService.ts` → `createSupabaseService(supabase)` from `@minute-menus/supabase-service`
- `services/geminiService.ts` → `@minute-menus/ai`
- `lib/database.types.ts` → `@minute-menus/types/db`
- `lib/currency.ts`, `lib/errorMessage.ts`, `lib/mailer.ts` → respective packages

## Where to put new code

| Need | Package |
|---|---|
| Shared type or enum | `@minute-menus/types` |
| DB column type change | Regenerate/copy into `packages/types/src/database.types.ts`, then service mappings |
| Reusable UI loader/button | `@minute-menus/ui` |
| Customer reel component | `@minute-menus/reels` |
| Pure analytics logic | `@minute-menus/metrics` |
| Menu or meal-plan DB sync | `@minute-menus/menu-persistence` or `meal-plan-persistence` |
| New Supabase service method | `@minute-menus/supabase-service` (split modules if file grows) |
| API route helper or email HTML | `@minute-menus/api-helpers` or `email-templates` |
| Payment provider logic | `@minute-menus/payments` |
| AI call | `@minute-menus/ai` |

Add `"@minute-menus/…": "workspace:*"` to root `package.json` when introducing a new package. Run **pnpm build** after wiring.

## Conventions

- Packages use `"exports"` in their `package.json`; no build step — TypeScript sources consumed directly by Vite.
- React packages (`ui`, `reels`) declare `react` / `react-dom` as peer dependencies.
- Server-only packages (`mailer`, `payments`, `api-helpers`) must not be imported from browser pages unless already safe (mailer is API-only today).
- Do not duplicate error helpers — always use `@minute-menus/errors`.
